prompt_template:
Create a {ASPECT_RATIO} image in the Neon Stadium 3D Hero Type Poster Style.

Subject: {SUBJECT}
Action: {SUBJECT_ACTION}
Prop/Product: {PRODUCT_OR_PROP}
Location: {LOCATION}
Background: {BACKGROUND_ELEMENTS}
Main text: {MAIN_TEXT}
Secondary text: {SECONDARY_TEXT}
Accent symbol: {ACCENT_SYMBOL}
Wardrobe/styling: {WARDROBE_STYLE}
Style fidelity anchors: {STYLE_FIDELITY_ANCHORS}
Source content to avoid: {SOURCE_CONTENT_TO_AVOID}

Apply these style rules as concrete visual direction: build a hyper-saturated 3D animated event-poster scene with one giant foreground hero, smaller supporting figures or props in deep perspective, a low wide-angle camera near the ground or action prop, and huge ultra-condensed uppercase typography cropped behind the figure. Use electric purple and acid lime as dominant poster colors, hot orange-red diagonal slashes, turquoise accent flashes, white glare, bright sky blue, stadium or arena light bloom, crisp rim highlights, controlled foreground motion blur, particles, sweat, dust, fabric mesh, gear scuffs, glossy toy-like skin, chunky simplified anatomy, expressive faces, and clean high-resolution tactile surfaces. Let the headline type act as a graphic wall behind the subject, partially blocked by the body and props. Use diagonal wedges and slice marks at corners and through letterforms. Keep the mood loud, heroic, playful, competitive, and commercial.

Avoid: soccer, soccer balls, FIFA, World Cup, 2026 event references, official marks, copied source slogans, copied jersey numbers, copied character poses, watermarks, platform marks, QR codes, creator signatures, flat vector substitutes, documentary realism, generic game screenshots, muddy AI grain, broken anatomy, and illegible text.

Important content rule: match the reference style first, then change the source content. Use new subjects, new scene details, new props or products, and new text while preserving the style fidelity anchors.
